defaultDame Patricia Hodgson:default DCMS seem to be taking forward the areas of most concern.  We talked about the appeals framework.  There are specific and detailed concerns about things like our powers in relation to consumers switching when a broadcasting package is involved, and we are in discussions with DCMS over that.  There are ongoing discussions about our powers in relation to due prominence on front pages and EPGs.  The DCMS is very willing and open to finding routes where possible to taking forward those issues that were felt to be of concern and might have been in legislation.
